div.p:
The State is divided into 104 counties. The following are the largest towns, with
                    population in 1880 Leavenworth, 16,550; Topeka, 15,451; Atchison, 15,106;
                    Lawrence, 8511; Wyandotte, 6149; Fort Scott, 5372; Wichita, 4911; Emporia, 4632;
                    Parsons, 4196; Ottawa, 4032. Topeka, the State capital, is advantageously
                    situated, and is one of the most flourishing towns in the State.
